org.dexpi.pid.xml

Class BsplineSurface

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dexpi.pid.xml.Surface
      • org.dexpi.pid.xml.BsplineSurface

  • public class BsplineSurface
extends Surface
    A BsplineSurface is general form of Rational or polynomial surface represented by control points, basis fuinctions and possibly weights.

      • getPresentationOrExtentOrControlPointArray

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> getPresentationOrExtentOrControlPointArray()
        Gets the value of the presentationOrExtentOrControlPointArray property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the presentationOrExtentOrControlPointArray property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getPresentationOrExtentOrControlPointArray().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<CTControlPointArray> JAXBElement<KnotMultiplicities> JAXBElement<CTWeights> JAXBElement<Knots> Extent JAXBElement<KnotMultiplicities> GenericAttributes Presentation JAXBElement<Knots>
